	"system": {
		"description": "<p>You continue to dive deep into your magical studies, searching for obscure magic where you can find it and broadening your horizons. You gain the following benefits:</p><ul><li><p>Your Dexterity, Constitution, or Intelligence score increases by +1, to a maximum of 20.</p></li><li><p>You learn an additional @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.1u4hyjbgjmvl22js]{Elective Study}.</p></li><li><p>When you cast one of your signature spells without using a spell slot, you gain temporary hit points equal to your proficiency bonus + your Intelligence modifier + the spell’s level. They last until you begin a short or long rest.</p></li><li><p>You gain proficiency with one artisan’s tool of your choice from alchemist’s supplies, calligrapher’s supplies, or cartographer’s tools.</p></li><li><p>The costs to research rare spells are reduced by 30% for you (this improves the discount from the previous feat, but does not stack with it).</p></li></ul>",
